Diff (+742/-83):
PR DESCRIPTION:
Following the lengthy discussion at https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/discussions/46915, this is a proposal to introduce a separate API for registering and retrieving values that are only known at runtime and differ from the original configured values.

There is a new `ValueRegistry` API  to retrieve such values, which allows you to either register single values or composed objects. A value can only be registered once per Quarkus run. There is only a single instance of `ValueRegistry` per Quarkus application, and it is non-static; it is created when the application starts. This allows you to retrieve the exact runtime of a running Quarkus application during testing in `RunningQuarkusApplication`. The `ValueRegistry` API is a separate module in `independent-projects/bootstrap/registry` set as `parent-first`, so it can be used between unrelated modules and avoid the Classloader dance to get a hold of it.  The actual implementation is sitting in `core/runtime`.

The `ValueRegistry` may be injected into a `Recorder` constructor wrapped with a `RuntimeValue` or retrieved via CDI. Since this isn't exactly a recordable object, I've used some tricks to pass it around, which we may want to review.

In terms of testing, the `ValueRegistry` is available in `@QuarkusTest` and `@QuarkusIntegrationTest` in the test storage. For `@QuarkusTest`, it retrieves directly the instance created by the running Quarkus application, and for `@QuarkusIntegrationTest`, it runs its own copy. I'v

